This tutorial explains how to create linux -> android-eabi, android-x86 cross compilers and compile the giac library.
The Kubuntu 14.04 system was used.

* Download Crystax NDK 10.2.1 from crystax.net/en/download
* unpack the contents to ~/android-sdks/
* set the enviroment variable NDK_DIR to ~/android-sdks/crystax-ndk-10.2.1/ and CC_DIR to ~/cross-compilers
*    ARCH=arm

  * $NDK_DIR/build/tools/make-standalone-toolchain --ndk-dir=$NDK_DIR --arch=$ARCH --platform=android-21 --install-dir=$CC_DIR/$ARCH
  * PATH=$CC_DIR/$ARCH/bin/:$PATH
  
  * (if needed) checkout gmp and mpf and make them with the following line
      ./configure --host=arm-linux-androideabi --prefix=$CC_DIR/$ARCH/sysroot/usr && make && make install

* repeat the process above for ARCH=x86

* uncomment the following lines in build.gradle
  //targetPlatform 'androideabi'
  //targetPlatform 'androidx86'

* call./gradlew :giac:androideabiJavagiacSharedLibrary :giac:androidx86JavagiacSharedLibrary  